						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1448 (1527 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that king <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇarāya</hi> caused the two doors of the entrance into the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> to be plated with gold and that <hi rend="bold">Īśvara,</hi> the brother of <hi rend="bold">Ananta</hi> of Bhāradvāja-gōtra, presented a circular <hi rend="italic">pīṭha</hi> to the god in the month of Phālguna in Vyaya. All these benefactions were done in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1448</hi> expressed by the chronograms <hi rend="italic">Jīvadvākyē</hi> and <hi rend="italic">dēvabhōgyē</hi> and which corresponded <hi rend="bold">to Vyaya (= 1526-27 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						</summary>
